Flow is a static type checker for Javascript. This is a list of Flow types generated from the source code in https://github.com/facebook/flow/tree/v0.35.0/ The script to generate this list is on github. Fixes welcome.

Note: I created a separate section for "private" or "magic" types with a $ in the name. See the note here and comment here.

Flow version: v0.35.0

  • Built-in types
  • Core
  • React
  • Document Object Model (DOM)
  • Browser Object Model (BOM)
  • CSS Object Model (CSSOM)
  • indexedDB
  • Node.js

  • Union and Intersection types

Built-in "private" types

  • $Diff<T,S>
  • $Exports<'M'> is the type of the exports of module 'M'
  • $Keys<T> is the set of keys of T
  • $NonMaybeType<T> acts as the type T without null and void
  • $PropertyType<T, 'x'> acts as the type of 'x' in object type T
  • $Shape<T> matches the shape of T
  • $Subtype<T> acts as any over subtypes of T
  • $Supertype<T> acts as any over supertypes of T
